Today, I joined @daveloebsack and @RepFinkenauer in calling on the Trump Administration to halt efforts to strike down the ACA. https://axne.house.gov/media/press-releases/iowa-democrats-call-trump-administration-halt-efforts-strike-down-aca …
We need to look at practical, bipartisan solutions to improve our healthcare system, lower costs, reduce burdens for small businesses and expand coverage across Iowa.

The ACA isn’t perfect. But overturning protections for Iowans with pre-existing conditions, reinstating life-time caps and going back to a time when insurers could charge women more is not the answer.

My heart is with everyone affected by the devastating flooding in Southwest Iowa. My office and I have been in touch with the Governor and her team, emergency management teams and Iowans who have lost their homes, businesses and farms.

The Iowa Disaster Behavioral Health Response Team is a trained team of volunteers who can respond to the mental health needs of Iowans following disasters. If you or a loved one is struggling or needs assistance, call: 515-725-3231. More info:  http://www.iowadbhrt.org/

For info on how to apply for IA Individual Disaster Assistance Grants, how to receive assistance to address disaster-related hardship, how to contact trained volunteers to assist w/ mental health needs following disaster, or how to report damages, visit:  https://www.iowa.gov/disaster-recovery-resources …
